11 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; amending 68
O.S. 2021, Section 2357.206, as amended by Section 1,
12 Chapter 49, O.S.L. 2022 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
2357.206), which relates to the Oklahoma Equal
13 Opportunity Education Scholarship Act; increasing
credit amount allowed for single individuals, married
14 individuals filing jointly, and legal business
entities; increasing credit amount for taxpayers who
15 contribute the same amount for an additional year;
modifying definition of eligible student; removing
16 federal law reference and replacing with Oklahoma
authority; modifying definition of low-income
17 eligible student; authorizing scholarship payments to
be made via secure electronic funds transfer;
18 modifying definition of annual revenue; requiring
certain annual reporting requirements to be
19 disaggregated into certain adjusted gross income
categories; and providing an effective date.
